Describe your favorite kind of weather
- what it is
- where you go in this weather
- what you do in this weather
- explain why you like it

I’d like to talk about my favorite kind of weather, which is a mildly cool day when it’s neither too hot nor too cold. Ideally, the temperature would be somewhere between 18 and 26 degrees Celsius, which I find very comfortable.

Since I tend to get sweaty quite easily, I really enjoy this kind of weather because it allows me to stay fresh and relaxed throughout the day. A perfect example of this climate can be found in Đà Lạt, a beautiful city in Vietnam that is well-known for its cool and pleasant weather all year round. I’ve visited it several times, and I always feel great whenever I’m there.

In this kind of weather, I usually spend more time outdoors. For example, I might go sightseeing, ride a bike, or simply sit at a café with friends and enjoy some hot drinks. It creates a very relaxing and enjoyable atmosphere.

There are several reasons why I prefer this type of weather. Firstly, it keeps me physically comfortable, as I don’t have to deal with excessive sweating or dehydration. Secondly, it gives me more flexibility in terms of clothing, as I can layer my outfits and dress more stylishly, which is difficult to do in hot weather. Finally, it’s perfect for a wide range of outdoor activities, making everyday life more enjoyable.

Overall, I find this kind of mild weather ideal, and if possible, I would love to live in a place with a similar climate in the future.
